Heres the problem...I finally got epic'd today  (YaY <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> ) and used the keyboard/macro controls of the new UI to bind my number 8 hotbank(epic) to the number 2 bank(flying kick).  Real easy to do, quick and painless.<br>
<br>
Now I know that it makes that same change for all hotbanks 1 through 10, no big deal there.  But when I log onto another character on the same account, those changes are still in affect, so I have to go back and change the macro so that the number 8 hotbank is tied to the number 8 on the keyboard.  And once I log on my monk have to do the change again...you get the point.<br>
<br>
Does anyone know of a way to set indvidual character macro's with the New UI?  As in when I play my monk the number 8 hotbank is tied to the number 2 bank.  But when I log on another character, its back to its original configuration.  It really isnt a chore to do the changes, just a bit annoying.  Just curious if by editing any of the UI files, or by some other stroke of genius this can be setup.<br>
